clinical_study.official_title: A Multicenter, Open-Label, Interventional Study to Evaluate Subject Satisfaction of AbobutulinumtoxinA Treatments in Moderate to Severe Glabellar Lines

brief_summary.textblock: An interventional Phase 4 study to assess subject satisfaction with abobotulinumtoxinA treatment.

detailed_description.textblock: Following signature of informed consent and the screening process, eligible subjects were treated at the Baseline visit (Day 0) with abobotulinumtoxinA in the glabellar region. Subjects were re-treated at the Month 6 visit.

primary_outcome.measure: Subject Satisfaction When Treated With abobutulinumtoxinA in Their Glabellar Lines
primary_outcome.description: Percentage of subjects satisfied with the treatment results assessed by satisfaction question at Month 12 visit.

secondary_outcome.measure: Subject Satisfaction With Aesthetic Outcome in Treated Area
secondary_outcome.description: based on Subject Satisfaction questionnaire data

secondary_outcome.measure: Evaluate Subject Satisfaction; Appraisal of Lines - Between Eyebrows
secondary_outcome.description: FACE-Q Appraisal of Lines: Between Eyebrows. Scored questionnaire to assess treatment outcome from subject's perspective. Minimum Rasch-transformed score = 0; Maximum Rasch-transformed score = 100. Higher score = better outcome.

secondary_outcome.measure: Evaluate the Impact of Treatment; Psychological Function
secondary_outcome.description: FACE-Q Psychological Function. Scored questionnaire to assess treatment outcome from subject's perspective. Minimum Rasch-transformed score = 0; Maximum Rasch-transformed score = 100. Higher score = better outcome.

secondary_outcome.measure: Subject Self-Assessment Using a 4-point Categorical Scale
secondary_outcome.description: Evaluate efficacy using a subject self-assessment scale that measures the severity of glabellar lines at maximum frown

secondary_outcome.measure: Investigator Live Assessment Using a 4-point Photographic Scale of Glabellar Line Severity
secondary_outcome.description: Evaluate efficacy at visits using a 4-point photographic scale of glabellar line severity, by Investigator Live assessment at maximum frown.

secondary_outcome.time_frame: After treatment at Baseline and Month 6, assessed up to 1 week after each treatment visit

intervention.description: AbobotulinumtoxinA treatment in the glabellar region at Baseline and Month 6

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Moderate to Severe Glabellar Lines at Maximum Frown
- Understands study requirements and signs an informed consent
Exclusion Criteria:
- Known allergy to any component of study product
- Pregnant or breast feeding or intending to get pregnant during the study
- Botulinum toxin treatment in the face within 9 months
